excerpt: Grand 57-hectare park featuring lawns, gardens, outdoor events & a monument to hero José Rizal.
detail_description: Rizal Park, also known as Luneta Park, is a sprawling 57-hectare urban park located in the heart of Manila. It is a popular destination for locals and tourists alike, offering lush lawns, vibrant gardens, and outdoor event spaces. The park is an ideal spot for picnics with its shady trees and expansive grassy areas.
name: Rizal Park
address: Ermita, Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: This landmark defensive fortress features a museum commemorating the national hero José Rizal.
detail_description: Fort Santiago is a historic defensive fortress located in Manila, Philippines. It was originally constructed in 1590 by Spanish conquistadors on the site of a pre-Hispanic king's palace. The fortress has been restored and now serves as a museum and public park within the Intramuros district. One of its main attractions is the Rizal Shrine, dedicated to national hero José Rizal who was imprisoned there before his execution in 1896.
name: Fort Santiago
address: Intramuros, Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Old-world Intramuros is home to Spanish-era landmarks like Fort Santiago, with a large stone gate and a shrine to national hero José Rizal. The ornate Manila Cathedral houses bronze carvings and stained glass windows, while the San Agustin Church museum has religious artwork and statues. Spanish colonial furniture and art fill Casa Manila museum, and horse-drawn carriages (kalesa) ply the area’s cobblestone streets.
detail_description: Intramuros, meaning "within the walls," is Manila's oldest neighborhood and historic heart. Built by the Spanish in the late 16th century, it has been a center of government, culture, and trade for over 350 years. Despite damage from wars and natural disasters, recent restoration efforts have preserved its colonial architecture.
name: Intramuros
address: Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Aquatic theme park & educational facility featuring hands-on activities, an oceanarium & live shows.
detail_description: Manila Ocean Park is a must-visit aquatic theme park and educational facility in Manila. It offers hands-on activities, an oceanarium with over 14,000 aquatic creatures from 270 species, including sharks, stingrays, jellyfish, and the first penguin facility in the country. The park also features live shows, exhibits, and an amusement park area. It's a great place for families to explore and learn about marine life while enjoying entertaining experiences.
name: Manila Ocean Park
address: 666 Behind, Quirino Grandstand, Ermita, City Of Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Historic church constructed starting in the 16th century with vaulted ceilings & detailed frescoes.
detail_description: The Archdiocesan Shrine of Our Lady of Consolation and Cincture, also known as San Agustin Church, is a historic church in Manila. Constructed in the 16th century, it features vaulted ceilings and detailed frescoes. It is one of the oldest churches in the Philippines and survived the Battle of Manila during World War II. Designated as a National Historical Landmark by the Philippine government and a UNESCO World Heritage Site, it holds significant historical value.
name: San Agustin Church
address: General Luna St, Intramuros, Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Binondo is a district in Manila and is referred to as the city's Chinatown. Its influence extends beyond to the places of Quiapo, Santa Cruz, San Nicolas and Tondo. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Binondo, also known as Manila's Chinatown, is a historic district in Manila and is considered the oldest Chinatown in the world. The name "Binondo" comes from the Tagalog word "binondoc," which means mountainous. Originally established for Chinese immigrants who converted to Catholicism, it has evolved into a bustling community with vibrant shopping streets and renowned restaurants serving authentic Chinese cuisine such as Peking duck and dumplings.
name: Binondo
address: Manila, 1006 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Massive museum with collections of Filipino fine art, archaeology, botany, natural history & more.
detail_description: The National Museum of Fine Arts is a significant cultural institution in the Philippines, showcasing an extensive collection of Filipino fine art, archaeology, botany, and natural history. As a government trust, it is dedicated to acquiring, preserving, and exhibiting works of art and historical artifacts that represent the rich cultural heritage of the Filipino people. The museum complex includes regional museums across the country and features renowned pieces such as the Spoliarium by Juan Luna.
name: National Museum of Fine Arts
address: Padre Burgos Ave, Ermita, Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Built in 1571, this historic church is known for its ornate architecture & visits by several popes.
detail_description: The Minor Basilica and Metropolitan Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception, also known as Manila Cathedral, is a historic church with ornate architecture dating back to 1571. It has been visited by several popes and is considered the Mother of all churches in the Philippines. The cathedral's Neo-Romanesque design, solemn ambiance, priceless relics, and stained glass windows make it a must-visit for both locals and tourists.
name: Minor Basilica and Metropolitan Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception - The Manila Cathedral
address: Cabildo, 132 Beaterio St, Intramuros, Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Star City is a well-known amusement park in Pasay that offers an exciting mix of thrilling rides and entertaining attractions suitable for all ages. The park features a variety of experiences, from adrenaline-pumping roller coasters to family-friendly carousels, ensuring there's something for everyone. In addition to the rides, visitors can enjoy live shows, game stalls, and delicious dining options. It's a perfect destination for a fun-filled day out with loved ones.
name: Star City
address: Roxas Blvd, CCP, Pasay City, 1300 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Modern museum for Filipino archeological artifacts, history & culture exhibits & a research library.
detail_description: Located in Makati, the Ayala Museum is a modern museum housed in a former stock exchange building. It showcases Filipino archaeological artifacts, history, and culture through six main permanent exhibitions. Visitors can explore traditional maritime vessels, embroidered silk garments from the 19th century elite, Chinese porcelain reflecting centuries of trade, and artworks by renowned Filipino artists like Fernando Zobel and Juan Luna.
name: Ayala Museum
address: Makati Avenue, corner Dela Rosa Street, Ayala Center, Makati City, 1229 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: This restored 1850s house is now a museum displaying Spanish colonial furniture, art & architecture.
detail_description: Casa Manila, a meticulously restored 1850s house turned museum, offers a glimpse into the opulent lifestyle of a wealthy Filipino family during the late Spanish colonial era. The facade is inspired by an actual residence from Binondo's Chinese district, while the interior showcases lavish European and Chinese furniture, crystal chandeliers, painted walls, and gilded furnishings that defined Manila houses of that period.
name: Casa Manila
address: plaza sans luis complex, General Luna St, Intramuros, Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Quiapo Church, like many other religious sites in Manila, has endured natural disasters and conflicts throughout its history. Despite these challenges, the church has maintained its Baroque facade featuring a grand pediment, twin towers, and Corinthian columns. However, visitors may be surprised by the modern interior with its sleek white design dating back to the 1980s.
name: Quiapo Church City Plaza
address: Church, Plaza, Miranda, Quiapo, City Of Manila, 1001 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Serene urban park built on a walled cemetery site with shaded paths & garden areas.
detail_description: Paco Park, originally a cemetery for affluent Spanish families in the Philippines, has transformed into a serene urban park with shaded paths and garden areas. It holds historical significance as the burial site of three priests executed in 1872. The park's lush surroundings make it popular for weddings, prenups, photoshoots, and romantic dates. Visitors can enjoy traditional music concerts and quiet strolls around the circular park. The Chapel of St.
name: Paco Park
address: HXJQ+99M, Belen, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Small urban park with a vast array of trees & plants, plus a fishpond & riverside walkway.
detail_description: Arroceros Forest Park, located in Manila, Philippines, is a small urban park developed in 1993. It spans 2.2 hectares and features a diverse range of trees and plants, including 61 tree varieties and 8,000 ornamental plants. The park is situated on the south bank of the Pasig River and offers a riverside walkway as well as a fishpond.
name: Arroceros Forest Park
address: 659 A Antonio Villegas St, Ermita, Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Robinsons Place Manila is a premier shopping destination in the Philippines, featuring seven storeys filled with premium and luxury brands in fashion, cosmetics, and more. The mall offers a wide range of entertainment options, retail stores, and gaming zones for visitors to enjoy. Additionally, guests can indulge in diverse dining options after a day of shopping. For those seeking unique experiences, the mall also provides bike lessons on its rooftop at The Tracks MNL by the NBO.
name: Robinsons Place Manila
address: Pedro Gil, cor Adriatico St, Ermita, Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Located in Tondo, Manila, Divisoria Public Market is a bustling institution offering a wide array of street food vendors, stalls selling clothing, accessories, handicrafts and fresh produce. The market is always crowded and bustling with vendors and shoppers on a spree for gadgets, fabrics, textiles, electronics and more at affordable prices. It's known for its knock-off fashion items and the opportunity to bargain with vendors.
name: Divisoria Public Market
address: 557 M. De Santos St, San Nicolas, Manila, 1010 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Manila, the capital of the Philippines, is a densely populated bayside city on the island of Luzon, which mixes Spanish colonial architecture with modern skyscrapers. Intramuros, a walled city in colonial times, is the heart of Old Manila. It’s home to the baroque 16th-century San Agustin Church as well as Fort Santiago, a storied citadel and former military prison.
detail_description: Manila, the bustling capital of the Philippines, is a vibrant city that seamlessly blends Spanish colonial architecture with modern skyscrapers. The historic walled city of Intramuros stands as the heart of Old Manila, boasting attractions like the San Agustin Church and Fort Santiago. Whether you're seeking a studio apartment in Quezon City or other vacation rentals in Manila, there are plenty of options to choose from for your stay.
name: City Of Manila
address: Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: 5.5-hectare zoo & garden featuring diverse animals in modest, old-fashioned enclosures.
detail_description: The Manila Zoological and Botanical Garden is a modest zoo with diverse animals in old-fashioned enclosures. It is one of the best places to see in Manila if travelling with kids.
name: Manila Zoo
address: HX7Q+W8H, Adriatico St, Malate, Manila, 1004 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: A lively, hip area, Makati’s Poblacion is home to backpacker lodgings, as well as the Rockwell Center with its upscale shops, and condo and office buildings. Nightlife centers on Kalayaan Avenue and surrounding streets, with dive bars and live-music venues, plus late-night eateries selling tacos and street food. Housed in a former town hall, Museo Ng Makati traces local history.
detail_description: Poblacion in Makati is a vibrant and trendy neighborhood that offers a mix of history, modern culture, and bustling nightlife. It features backpacker lodgings alongside upscale shops, condo buildings, and office spaces. The area's nightlife scene is centered around Kalayaan Avenue with dive bars, live music venues, and late-night eateries serving up delicious street food.
name: Poblacion
address: Makati City, Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Bordered by open-air cafes, this long, bayside walkway is a popular place to watch the sunset.
detail_description: Manila Baywalk Dolomite Beach is a popular bayside walkway that offers stunning sunset views over Manila Bay. This two-kilometer promenade stretches from the American Embassy to the Cultural Center of the Philippines, lined with palm trees and open-air cafes. The area holds historical significance as it was the site of the Battle of Manila Bay in 1898.
name: Manila Bay Beach
address: Roxas Blvd, Malate, Manila, 1004 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Zoological, botanical & geological specimens displayed in an elegant venue with a soaring atrium.
detail_description: The National Museum of Natural History is a stunning venue that showcases zoological, botanical, and geological specimens. It opened on International Museum Day and features the majestic Tree of Life in its courtyard. Visitors can enjoy a 360-degree view from the scenic elevator and explore galleries such as Mangroves, Beaches and Intertidal Zones, The Marine Realm, Natural Inheritance, and Temporary Exhibitions.
name: National Museum of Natural History
address: Teodoro F. Valencia Cir, Ermita, Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Makati is a city in the Philippines’ Metro Manila region and the country’s financial hub. It’s known for the skyscrapers and shopping malls of Makati Central Business District, and for Ayala Triangle Gardens, an area dotted with trees and sculptures. Ayala Museum houses the Filipinas Heritage Library and craft collections documenting the country’s history. The Rizal Monument is a memorial to national hero José Rizal.
detail_description: Makati, a bustling city in the Metro Manila region of the Philippines, is renowned as the country's financial epicenter. The Makati Central Business District stands out with its impressive skyscrapers and upscale shopping malls, while Ayala Triangle Gardens offers a serene escape with its lush greenery and captivating sculptures. Visitors can delve into Filipino history at Ayala Museum and pay homage to national hero José Rizal at the Rizal Monument.
name: Makati City
address: Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Presidential museum & library showcasing Philippine politics, culture & history, with tours.
detail_description: Malacañan Palace, located in San Miguel on Mendiola Street, is a significant historical site in the Philippines. It served as the residence of Ferdinand and Imelda Marcos for two decades until they were ousted during the People Power demonstration in 1986. Originally built by a Spanish aristocrat, it was later expanded and renovated by the Marcoses. The palace has undergone various transformations throughout history, including an exorcism performed when Aquino came to power.
name: Malacañang Palace
address: Jose P Jose Laurel St, San Miguel, Manila, Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Modern, dome-shaped Catholic church with open sides, set in a tree-filled park amid skyscrapers.
detail_description: Sto. Nino de Paz Greenbelt Chapel, also known as the Chapel of Santo Nino de Paz, is a modern Catholic church located in Manila. Surrounded by skyscrapers, this dome-shaped church stands out with its open sides and lush greenery. The architecture of the chapel is a major attraction for tourists, featuring a roof that resembles a soldier's cap and serene ponds and sculptures that create a peaceful atmosphere amidst the city's hustle and bustle.
name: Sto. Nino de Paz Greenbelt Chapel
address: Ayala Center, Makati City, Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Baywalk is a charming pedestrian walkway along Roxas Blvd that offers breathtaking sunset views of Manila Bay. It's a great spot to soak in the local atmosphere and enjoy the vibrant surroundings.
name: Baywalk
address: Malate, City Of Manila, 1004 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Chinatown, specifically Ongpin St in Binondo, is a vibrant and bustling area that offers a mix of modern conveniences and traditional charm. The popular hole-in-the-wall eateries serve handmade delicacies with stunning flavors, making the long queues worth the wait. Visitors can explore the oldest Chinatown in the world, where they'll find a gritty yet remarkable place filled with new sights to see.
name: Chinatown
address: 913 Ongpin St, Santa Cruz, Manila, 1003 Kalakhang Maynila, Philippines

detail_description: The Cultural Center of the Philippines, designed by the renowned architect Leandro V. Locsin, stands as a testament to his modernist concrete designs. This iconic structure is a significant part of the country's architectural heritage and is a key component of the nation's cultural landscape.
name: Cultural Center of the Philippines
address: HX5M+5CM, Pedro Bukaneg St, Malate, Manila, 1004 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Catholic church containing a revered 17th-century statue of Jesus called the Black Nazarene.
detail_description: The Minor Basilica & National Shrine of Jesus Nazareno, also known as Quiapo Church, is a significant Catholic church in Manila. It houses the revered 17th-century Black Nazarene statue, attracting devoted worshippers who believe in its miraculous powers. The church's iconic architecture, designed by Juan Nakpil, features a spacious dome and imposing belfries.
name: Minor Basilica and National Shrine of Jesus Nazareno - St. John the Baptist Parish (Archdiocese of Manila)
address: 910 Plaza Miranda, Quiapo, Manila, 1001 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Sprawling shopping complex around a leafy garden & ponds, with eateries & movie theaters.
detail_description: Greenbelt is a sprawling shopping complex nestled around a lush garden and serene ponds, offering an array of eateries and movie theaters. The Santo Nino de Paz, also known as the Greenbelt Chapel, is a stunning hidden gem within the mall, featuring a distinctive low dome shape and surrounded by water and greenery.
name: Greenbelt
address: Legazpi Street, Legazpi Village, Makati City, Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Old downtown street established in 1594, with art deco buildings, pop-up shops & cafes.
detail_description: Escolta St, established in 1594, is one of Manila's oldest streets. It was once the heart of the city's Central Business District and home to the Manila Stock Exchange. While many businesses have moved, Escolta still boasts impressive art deco buildings like Regina Building and Capitol Theater. The street got its name from Spanish word for 'escort' during the British occupation when military escorts would pass through.
name: Escolta St
address: Manila, Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Serene, triangle-shaped park with jogging paths, adjacent eateries & seasonal light shows.
detail_description: Ayala Triangle Gardens is a hidden gem nestled in the vibrant heart of Makati's central business district. This tranquil, triangle-shaped park spans 2 hectares and serves as a peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of city life. Surrounded by towering skyscrapers, it features beautifully landscaped lawns, tree-lined paths perfect for jogging or leisurely strolls, and ample open spaces ideal for picnics or casual gatherings.
name: Ayala Triangle Gardens
address: Paseo De Roxas St Cor Makati Ave, Cor Ayala Ave, Makati City, 1209 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Manila Baywalk is a popular spot for tourists to visit in Manila. It's easily accessible from Ninoy Aquino International Airport, which offers direct flights from various international destinations. While the sunset at Manila Bay may not be as dramatic as in other places, it still offers a glorious view that will take your breath away. The best place to catch this stunning sight is along the bay walk in Mall of Asia, where you can also enjoy people-watching and explore significant spots within the mall area.
name: Manila Baywalk
address: Roxas Blvd, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila, Philippines

name: Quiapo Church City Plaza
address: Church, Plaza, Miranda, Quiapo, Manila, 1001 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Museum & heritage center exploring contributions & influences of the Chinese in Philippine culture.
detail_description: Bahay Tsinoy, Museum of Chinese in Philippine Life is a heritage center located in Intramuros, Manila that delves into the rich history and cultural influence of the Chinese community in the Philippines. The museum showcases the early exchanges and arrivals of the Chinese dating back to the 9th century, their itinerant lifestyle during colonial times, and their significant contributions to the industrialization of the country.
name: Bahay Tsinoy, Museum of Chinese in Philippine Life
address: 32 Anda St, Intramuros, Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Intramuros, also known as the Walled City, is a must-visit destination in Manila that offers a captivating journey through the city's rich history and culture. This 16th-century stone citadel is filled with iconic landmarks such as the San Agustin Church, Manila Cathedral, Fort Santiago, and Baluarte de San Diego.
name: Intramuros
address: HXRC+JP, Intramuros, Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Explore the vibrant and historic Chinatown Walk, located just a 15-minute walk from Manila Cathedral. This charming area features narrow streets and a bustling atmosphere, offering an authentic glimpse into Filipino-Chinese culture. While it may not be ideal for shopping, visitors can indulge in delicious noodles and other culinary delights. Discover the oldest Chinatown outside of China, boasting rich cultural traditions and a thriving food scene.
name: ChinaTown Walk
address: Binondo, City Of Manila, 1006 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Store specializing in traditional woven bags within a multilevel mall in a popular shopping area.
detail_description: Divisoria Mall, specifically the three-storey 168 Shopping Mall, is a popular shopping destination in Manila. It offers a wide range of products at incredibly affordable prices, making it a go-to for locals looking for bargains. From traditional woven bags to shoes, clothes, tools, party favors, and souvenirs, this mall has it all. Visitors can expect to find the cheapest prices for specific items and enjoy a diverse selection of products with good quality.
name: Divisoria Mall
address: 866 Tabora St, Binondo, City Of Manila, Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Built in 1976, this museum features contemporary Filipino art, plus some historical artifacts.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Bonifacio Global City, the Metropolitan Museum of Manila stands as a beacon of modern and contemporary Filipino art. Established in 1976, this non-profit institution initially aimed to introduce Filipinos to global artistic expressions through its diverse collection. Over the years, it has evolved into a premier venue for showcasing both local talents and international artists alike.
name: Metropolitan Museum of Manila at BGC
address: 30th St, Taguig, Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Stately, neoclassical museum housing a broad collection of Filipino cultural materials & artifacts.
detail_description: The National Museum of Anthropology, located within the National Museum complex in Manila, offers a comprehensive exploration of Filipino cultural history. This stately neoclassical museum showcases a diverse collection of artifacts and materials that provide insight into the sociological, linguistic, and economic aspects of the Philippines and its people. Visitors can marvel at traditional textiles, ancient baybayin scripts, and centuries-old maritime and ivory trade relics.
name: National Museum of Anthropology
address: HXPJ+3C6, P. Burgos Drive Rizal Park, Teodoro F. Valencia Cir, Ermita, Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Museum with a collection of artifacts & artwork in a former monastery adjacent to a landmark church.
detail_description: The San Agustin Convent Museum is located adjacent to the iconic San Agustin Church, a UNESCO World Heritage Site in Manila. The museum is housed in a former monastery that was rebuilt after being destroyed during World War II. It offers a rich collection of historical artifacts and artwork, providing insight into the Philippines' colonial past and the history of the Catholic faith in the country.
name: San Agustin Convent Museum
address: HXQF+JXP, General Luna St, Intramuros, City Of Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: A wide range of cultural events are staged at this major government-run institution.
detail_description: Located in Manila, the Cultural Center of the Philippines Complex houses theaters that regularly stage ballets and plays as well as art galleries. This imposing 1969 building was designed by Leandro V. Locsin in the style of Bagong Lipunan Modernism, and it is a sight to behold.
name: Cultural Center of the Philippines
address: CCP Complex, Roxas Blvd, Pasay City, 1300 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Nestled within the Cultural Center of the Philippines, the Coconut Palace stands as a remarkable testament to Filipino ingenuity and architectural evolution. Constructed predominantly from various parts of the coconut palm, this unique structure—also known as Tahanang Pilipino or Filipino Home—was commissioned in 1978 by former First Lady Imelda Marcos to serve as an official residence for the Vice President.
name: Coconut Palace
address: Roxas Boulevard, Malate, City Of Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Massive museum with collections of Filipino fine art, archaeology, botany, natural history & more.
name: National Museum of Fine Arts
address: Padre Burgos Ave, Ermita, City Of Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

name: Central Bank Money Museum
address: BSP Main Complex, P A. Mabini St, Malate, City Of Manila, 1004 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Luneta, also known as Rizal Park, offers a peaceful retreat for nature enthusiasts within the bustling city. The park's expansive green areas provide a serene escape from urban life, making it an ideal destination for those seeking tranquility amidst the metropolis.
name: Luneta
address: 666, Ermita, Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Landmark granite church with a 16th-century bell tower, featuring regular masses & self-led tours.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Manila's vibrant Chinatown, the Minor Basilica and National Shrine of Saint Lorenzo Ruiz, commonly known as Binondo Church, is a historic gem that dates back to 1596. This stunning granite church features a striking 16th-century bell tower and offers regular masses in multiple languages including Filipino, Mandarin, Hokkien, and English.
name: Minor Basilica and National Shrine of Saint Lorenzo Ruiz - Binondo Church (Archdiocese of Manila)
address: 1006 Plaza Lorenzo Ruiz, Binondo, 1006 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Built in 1891, this striking Gothic church has steel vaulting, stained-glass windows & 2 towers.
detail_description: The Minor Basilica of San Sebastian and Archdiocesan Shrine of Our Lady of Mount Carmel in the Archdiocese of Manila is a stunning Gothic church constructed in 1891. It features remarkable steel vaulting, beautiful stained-glass windows, and two impressive towers. The basilica is renowned for being the only church in Asia made entirely out of steel, making it a must-visit destination for those embarking on Visita Iglesia.
name: Minor Basilica of San Sebastian and Archdiocesan Shrine of Our Lady of Mount Carmel (Archdiocese of Manila)
address: Pasaje del Carmen St, Quiapo, City Of Manila, 1001 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Prison where 19th-century national hero Jose Rizal was held, now a museum with books & artwork.
detail_description: The Rizal Shrine at Fort Santiago is a significant historical site in Manila, Philippines. It was originally a citadel built by Spanish conquistador Miguel Lopez de Legazpi and served as a prison during the Spanish Colonial Period and World War II. The museum within the fort houses a collection of Jose Rizal's memorabilia, including his prison cell and trial room. Visitors can also see replicas of his ancestral house and follow his final footsteps to the execution ground.
name: Rizal Shrine
address: Fort Santiago, General Luna St, Intramuros, City Of Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: The Memorare - Manila 1945 Monument is a sculpture dedicated to the innocent civilians who lost their lives during the Battle of Manila in 1945. The monument is located in the heart of Manila, and is a popular spot for tourists and locals to visit. The monument is also a historical marker, and helps keep the memory of these tragic events alive.
name: Manila 1945 Memorial
address: HXRF+5QC, General Luna St, Intramuros, 658 Zone 70, Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Established interactive children's museum featuring hands-on exhibits & theatrical shows.
detail_description: Museo Pambata, situated in Manila near Rizal Park, is a unique interactive museum tailored for children. It features eight themed rooms that cover various topics such as environment, old Manila, career options, love for the planet Earth, human body, marketplace dynamics, global village and child rights. Unlike traditional museums where artifacts are kept behind glass shelves, Museo Pambata encourages hands-on exploration through its exhibits.
name: Museo Pambata
address: Roxas Boulevard, cor South Drive, Manila, Philippines
